[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1887[0m:[38;5;10m[49m What can go wrong if you skip or shortcut this: the discharge-to-home gap (the 48-hour-to-72-hour window where most preventable readmissions originate) is unmanaged, medication reconciliation is left to chance, follow-up appointments are not validated against the protocol window, red-flag warnings are not delivered, and the transition closure is silent. Transitions of care are the single most consequential coordination event class for this assistant, and they are best run through a deterministic state-machine orchestration rather than left to LLM judgment.
